==English==
===Verb===
'''[[take]] [[out]] [[the]] [[stop]]s'''
# {{finance}} The supposed practice whereby [[local]]s (floor traders trading for their own account) buy or sell to push prices towards where they suspect [[stop loss order]]s lie, with a view to profiting from the resulting acceleration of the move when those orders hit the market.
#: 2006: ''Chris Towner, consultant at risk manager HIFX, said: "The move came when traders looked at each other and said 'it's about time we broke out of these ranges', and took out the stops."'' &mdash; [[w:Financial Times|Financial Times]] article ''Euro gains from dollar's slump'' by Steve Johnson, 5 April 2006, reproduced at HiFX [http://www.hifx.co.uk/press/articles/05042006.htm]